# =============================================================================
# CodeRouter — USER CONFIG TEMPLATE (safe to commit, no real secrets)
# =============================================================================
# This file has PLACEHOLDERS only. It is meant to be copied → .env on your machine.
#
#   NEVER add real API keys to this file and never commit .env to git.
#
# Quick copy (run inside the coderouter repo folder):
#   Windows CMD:     copy install-global-skills.example.env .env
#   PowerShell:      Copy-Item install-global-skills.example.env .env
#   macOS / Linux:  cp install-global-skills.example.env .env
#
# Then edit .env and replace every placeholder below with your real values.
# Same layout as .env.example — use either file as your starting point.
#
# Next: node install-global-skills.js   (and restart your terminal after it finishes)
# =============================================================================

# --- Required ---
# OpenRouter: https://openrouter.ai/settings/keys
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-v1-replace-with-your-openrouter-key

# Default free router (change to any model id from https://openrouter.ai/models )
CLAUDE_MODEL=openrouter/free

# --- Optional: @21st-dev/magic MCP ---
# Get a key at https://21st.dev then either:
#   npm run setup:21st   (interactive), or uncomment and set MAGIC_API_KEY below.
# Then: node install-global-skills.js
#   - Requires ~/.claude.json (open Claude Code once if the file does not exist yet).
#   - Installer adds user-scope MCP at ~/.claude.json → top-level mcpServers (all folders).
#   - Restart Claude Code / IDE after install; verify with: claude mcp list
# MAGIC_API_KEY=your-key-here

# Optional: write proxy-debug.log (only if you need to trace requests)
# CODEROUTER_PROXY_DEBUG=1

# Vision fallback when the proxy cannot pick a free vision model dynamically
VISION_MODEL=qwen/qwen-2.5-vl-72b-instruct:free
